**Description**
When setting the timeout to 5000, I would expect that the failure callback of the http Promise will be called after 5 seconds.

It works as expected on iOS and Android 6, 7, ... but not on Android 4 and Android 5.

```
httpModule.request({
        url: "http://www.mocky.io/v2/5be3174d2f00007b00ca2260?mocky-delay=10000ms",
        timeout: 5000,
        method: "GET",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" }
    }).then((response) => {
        alert({title: "Alert", message: "Received response: " + response.content, okButtonText: "Close"});
    }, (e) => {
        alert({title: "Alert", message: "" + e, okButtonText: "Close"});
    }
});
```

**To Reproduce**
<!-- Add commands used or steps taken to reproduce the behaviour. -->
Open the sample app, tap the button to start the http request and after 5 seconds you should see the error message on Android 6+ and on iOS, but on Android 4 and 5 it will continue until 20 seconds.

**Expected behavior**
The failure part of the promise in http.request(...) should be called after the time defined for the timeout-property (in the sample app: 5 seconds).

**Sample project**
[NSHttpTimeout.zip](https://github.com/NativeScript/NativeScript/files/4251092/NSHttpTimeout.zip)

