**Describe the bug**
UiNavigationBar can't be modified in `ActionBar.loadedEvent` event handler.

**To Reproduce**
Create a new project (tested with react-nativescript and plain TypeScript project - hello world starter template). Set an id for ActionBar and add an event handler to it - *in the page navigatingTo function code behind...*

```
    const actionBar = page.getViewById("actionBar") as ActionBar;
    actionBar.addEventListener(ActionBar.loadedEvent, (event) => {
        // (actionBar.ios as UINavigationBar).topItem.title = "I wwaaas changed"; // does not work
        setTimeout(() => {
            (actionBar.ios as UINavigationBar).topItem.title = "I wwaaas changed"; // works
        }, 0.000000001);
    });
```

 
**Expected behavior**
The changes to the ActionBar on iOS - UINavigationBar should take effect following `ActionBar.loadedEvent`.

**Additional context**
I have tested changing a plenty UINavigationBar values in react-nativescript and only the `topitem.title` in plain typescript project. Have not tested on Android.

